ted> 1685113574</ingested><modified> 2023-05-26T15:06:41+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Shopping]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jeff Dunn]]></category><media:content height="675" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-07/9fd76450-f93c-11ec-b745-5e8b1b526e29" width="1200"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="675" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-07/9fd76450-f93c-11ec-b745-5e8b1b526e29" width="1200"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Solo Stove]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A Solo Stove fire pit sitting on grass next to fire wood and an American flag at a backyard party.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Solo Stove]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Swiss researchers use a wireless BCI to help a spinal injury patient walk more naturally]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>每年，<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5399137/">北美有超过 100 万人</a>遭受某种形式的脊髓损伤 (SCI)，每年用于治疗和康复这些患者的费用超过 70 亿美元。在过去的四分之一个世纪中，医学界<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.facs.org/for-medical-professionals/news-publications/news-and-articles/acs-brief/may-31-2022-issue/clinical-trials-show-promising-future-for-management-of-spinal-cord-injuries/">在减轻（如果不是逆转）瘫痪的影响方面取得了令人难以置信的进展，</a>包括药理学、 <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.anl.gov/article/fixing-spinal-cord-injuries-with-dancing-molecules">干细胞技术</a>、神经调节和外部假肢方面的进步。脊髓的电刺激在帮助脊髓损伤患者康复方面已经显示出特别有希望的结果，不仅可以改善肢体功能，还可以改善痉挛、膀胱和血压控制。现在，在周二发表在<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Nature Research;elmt:;cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=c6c965be-a8ea-473d-89f4-9754f2675a60&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Nature+Research&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJjNmM5NjViZS1hOGVhLTQ3M2QtODlmNC05NzU0ZjI2NzVhNjAiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubmF0dXJlLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9zNDE1ODYtMDIzLTA2MDk0LTUiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjNmMjg0ZDZmLWQ2OTUtNDAzMy1hZThjLTQ4YjFlZDYyMWQ0YSJ9&amp;signature=AQAAARRg19BpulsoF3FtuK00Y2ibUzY0pDe8It3eW1uRxdCR&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fs41586-023-06094-5" class="rapid-with-clickid"><em>《自然》</em></a>杂志上的一项研究中， <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.onwd.com/#Top">SCI 治疗初创公司 Onward Medical</a>宣布，它通过使用植入式脑机接口 (BCI) 和跨越大脑的新型“数字桥”，帮助改善了一名前截瘫患者的行走步态脊柱被切断的缝隙。</p><p>多年来，作为身体康复的一部分，我们一直在使用低压电击来刺激截瘫患者的脊柱，这一过程被称为<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Mayo Clinic;elmt:;cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=e1fe4ee4-58fb-4e08-bb86-6b27247202b1&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Mayo+Clinic&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAa1F7cTqM1WKn4o6LE2zB1B25Xhr8QE8Y78hAtnm32fK&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mayoclinic.org%2Ftests-procedures%2Ffunctional-electrical-stimulation-for-spinal-cord-injury%2Fabout%2Fpac-20394230" class="rapid-with-clickid">功能性电刺激</a>(FES)。电极直接放置在它们要刺激的神经上方——从外部绕过它们自身被破坏的神经通路——并且当被激活时，会导致下面的神经放电并且它们的肌肉收缩。研究人员已经使用这种方法在一些患者身上<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.washington.edu/news/2021/01/12/treatment-allows-some-people-with-spinal-cord-injury-regain-hand-and-arm-function/">恢复了手和手臂的运动</a>，在其他人身上<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2018-09-25-electronic-implant-paralyzed-people-walk-again.html">恢复了站立和行走的能力</a>，对于少数幸运的人来说，还可以<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.cea.fr/english/Pages/An-unprecedented-neuroprosthetic-allows-a-tetraplegic-patient-fitted-with-an-exoskeleton-to-move.aspx">穿上套装</a>！然而，由此产生的肢体动作显然是不优雅的，导致笨重的手臂动作和更像洗牌的步行步态。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> Onward <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Nature Research;elmt:;cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=c6c965be-a8ea-473d-89f4-9754f2675a60&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Nature+Research&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJjNmM5NjViZS1hOGVhLTQ3M2QtODlmNC05NzU0ZjI2NzVhNjAiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubmF0dXJlLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9zNDE1ODYtMDE4LTA2NDktMiIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiM2YyODRkNmYtZDY5NS00MDMzLWFlOGMtNDhiMWVkNjIxZDRhIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAb1XCQEeUOn7346wn9o4_0smzaMKW_N_4l4cxoZIatbf&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fs41586-018-0649-2" class="rapid-with-clickid">早期对硬膜外电刺激的研究</a>表明，它可以有效地瞄准可用于触发腿部肌肉的下背部神经。但当时的治疗受到可穿戴运动传感器需求的阻碍，而且“参与者……使腿部运动适应不断变化的地形和意志需求的能力有限。”在周二的研究中，Onward 通过结合“数字桥”解决了这个问题” 来监测大脑的命令冲动，并以无线方式实时将它们传送到植入患者下背部的刺激包。</p><p>在过去十年的大部分时间里，临床医生一直在使用这些系统来帮助改善 SCI 后的上肢控制和功能——Onward 自己的<a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.med-technews.com/news/medical-device-news/onward-medical-granted-fda-breakthrough-device-designation/">ARC EX 系统</a>就是为此而设计的——尽管这项研究是第一个将相同的理论应用于下肢的研究四肢。</p><p> Onward 的患者是一名 38 岁的男性，他在十年前曾遭受过“不完全性颈椎 (C5/C6) 脊髓损伤”，并接受了为期五个月的“脊髓硬膜外电刺激”神经康复计划2017 年。“这个项目使他能够在前轮助行器的帮助下重新获得行走的能力，”研究团队在<em>《自然》杂志</em>的研究中指出。 “尽管在家里继续使用刺激，大约三年后，他已经达到了神经恢复的平稳期。”</p><p>除了 EX 之外，Onward Medical 还开发了一种内部安装的电刺激疗法，即 ARC IM。根据该公司的说法，它“专门用于沿着脊髓放置以刺激<a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dorsal_root_of_spinal_nerve">背根</a>”，以帮助改善 SCI 患者的血压调节。周二研究中使用的系统以 ARC IM 为基础，并将其与<a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fnins.2019.00847/full">WIMAGINE 脑机接口</a>相结合。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-05/7c48a010-fb3b-11ed-8e76-f7a01d9e0cb0" style="height:850px;width:2123px;" alt="图。1" data-uuid="1968027c-4019-3496-a13d-d14b5764d038"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">安华医疗</div></figure><p>Onward 团队必须首先将 BCI 安装在患者的颅骨内。从技术上讲，它是一对 64 引线电极植入物，每个植入物都安装在一个 50 毫米的圆形钛金属外壳中，与头骨齐平。 WIMAGINE“比其他选择侵入性更小，同时提供足够的分辨率来驱动步行，”OnwardMedical 首席执行官 Dave Marver 通过电子邮件告诉 Engadget。 “它还有五年的数据，证明所产生信号的清晰度是稳定的。”</p><p>两个外部天线位于头皮上，第一个通过电感耦合为植入物供电，第二个将信号分流到便携式基站进行解码和处理。然后将处理后的信号无线传输到位于患者腰部上方<a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://www.medtronic.com/uk-en/patients/treatments-therapies/neurostimulator-essential-tremor/activa-rc.html">的 ACTIVA RC 植入式脉冲发生器</a>，在该发生器中，另外 16 个植入的电极会刺激适当的神经簇以移动他们的腿部。根据 Onward，它们一起构成了一个脑脊柱接口 (BSI) 系统。</p><p>整个设置旨在供患者独立使用。助行器包含所有 BSI 零件，而触觉反馈界面可帮助他们正确定位耳机并校准预测算法。</p><p>为了让 BCI 和脉冲发生器无缝地协同工作，Onward 利用了“Aksenova/Markov 切换多线性算法，将<a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://ecog-acrin.org/resources/ecog-performance-status">ECoG</a>信号与硬膜外电刺激参数的控制联系起来”，事后看来这很明显。基本上，该算法预测两件事：患者根据其监测的信号打算移动特定关节的概率，以及假定的预期运动的幅度和方向。然后将这些预测转储到一个模拟控制器中，该控制器将它们转换为代码命令，这些命令又每 300 毫秒循环一次到脉冲发生器。总而言之，患者思考“我应该走过去”与系统解码这些想法之间的延迟仅为 1.1 秒。 </p><div id="bf690dc27d044e5cbf1340e22b18409e"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/mR-049IX4cc?rel=0" style="top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;position:absolute;border:0;" allowfullscreen scrolling="no"></iframe></div><p>事实证明，为患者校准系统也是一个同样快速的过程。患者在尝试的前两分钟内就想出了如何正确“激活”臀部肌肉以产生足够的扭矩来摆动双腿的方法——而且准确率高达 97%。在康复过程中，患者成功地控制了腿部每个关节（臀部、膝盖和脚踝）的运动，平均准确度（因为 BSI 完成了患者的意图）约为 75%。</p><p> “仅经过 5 分钟的校准，BSI 支持对髋屈肌活动的持续控制，”该团队继续说道，“与没有 BSI 的尝试相比，这使参与者的肌肉活动增加了五倍”不幸的是，这些收益他们解释说，一旦 BCI 关闭，它们就会消失，立即失去行走的能力。 “一旦 BSI 重新打开，步行就会恢复。”</p><p>得益于此手术，患者不仅能够从使用前轮助行器行走过渡到使用拐杖行走——他们的行走步态也得到了显着改善。 “与单独的刺激相比，BSI 使行走的步态特征明显更接近健康个体的量化特征，”Onward 团队写道。患者甚至可以使用该系统拄着拐杖穿越未铺砌的地形，这一壮举仍然经常被证明对许多双足机器人来说是危险的。</p><p>总之，患者接受了 40 次 BCI 康复训练——标准物理康复与 BCI 支持的平衡、步行和运动锻炼相结合。患者的感官（轻触）分数有所提高，但<a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1" href="https://scireproject.com/outcome/wisci-and-wisci-ii">WISCI II 分数</a>却增加了 10 分之多。 WISCI II 是脊髓损伤的步行指数，一个 21 分的量表，测量患者的行走能力，范围从 20“可以移动零辅助”到 0“卧床不起”。Onward 的患者从 6 到 16在这种疗法的帮助下。</p><p> Onward 团队写道：“由于参与者之前在仅使用脊髓刺激进行强化康复后已经达到了恢复的平稳期，因此可以合理地假设 BSI 触发了负责额外神经恢复的神经元通路重组。” “这些结果表明，在大脑和脊髓之间建立持续联系可以促进在正常生理条件下连接这两个区域的残余神经元通路的重组。”</p><p>尽管结果令人鼓舞，但仍有许多工作要做。 Onward 团队认为，未来的迭代将需要“基站、计算单元和不易察觉的天线的小型化”、更快的数据吞吐量、“多功能刺激参数、来自可穿戴计算单元的直接无线控制”以及“单个低功耗集成电路”嵌入具有自校准功能的神经形态处理器，可自动将皮层活动转化为刺激程序的更新。”</p><p>尽管存在艰巨的技术挑战，“周二<em>自然</em>出版物中描述的 BCI 系统可能会在五到七年内进入市场，”Marvel 预测。 “到本世纪末，BCI 增强脊髓刺激疗法将上市是可能的，也是现实的。”</p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/swiss-researchers-help-a-spinal-injury-patient-to-walk-more-naturally-using-a-wireless-bci-151542965.html ?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/swiss-researchers-help-a-spinal-injury-patient-to-walk-more-naturally-using-a-wireless-bci-151542965.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 3f284d6f-d695-4033-ae8c-48b1ed621d4a</guid><dc:creator>安德鲁·塔兰托拉</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Fri, 26 May 2023 15:15:42 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1685107847</ingested><modified> 2023-05-26T13:30:54+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Health]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Andrew Tarantola]]></category><media:content height="1772" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-05/135185c0-fb3d-11ed-bdfe-becad6262ea7" width="2881"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1772" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-05/135185c0-fb3d-11ed-bdfe-becad6262ea7" width="2881"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Swiss researchers use a wireless BCI to help a spinal injury patient walk more naturally]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best DACs for Apple Music Lossless in 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> “苹果效应”既有帮助，也可能令人恼火。一项好的技术可以存在多年，在获得库比蒂诺批准之前，许多人不会在意。为此，随着该公司向大众推出<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-music-lossless-now-available-on-supported-devices-094540982.html">升级版音乐服务，</a>很多人开始关心“高分辨率”数字音频。</p><p>但正如许多人很快指出的那样，苹果自己的一些产品<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-music-lossless-explained-153046070.html">不一定支持</a>所提供的更高采样率和位深度。不用担心，有一个加密狗。 （还有适用于 Android 和桌面的选项。）</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>正如暗示的那样，参与高分辨率游戏的不仅仅是 Apple： <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-11-11-qobuz-drops-lossy-music-streaming.html">Qobuz</a> 、 <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-12-12-tidal-hifi-dolby-atmos-music.html">Tidal</a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-11-18-deezer-hifi-on-mobile-and-web.html">Deezer</a>已经这样做了一段时间， <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/spotify-hifi-select-markets-premium-cd-quality-audio-2021-165438547.html">Spotify</a>也计划很快推出自己的版本。除了 Tidal 的 MQA 之外，本指南中的产品将与这些服务中的任何一个配合得很好，后者更具体一些（我们也有相应的选项）。</p><h2>为什么我需要新硬件来听音乐？ </h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-06/2cc73eb0-c9de-11eb-afdf-c4eb8bff6f7b" alt="适用于 Apple Music Lossless 2021 的最佳 DAC" data-uuid="c78a9cea-212d-3e34-94be-5d75682f084a"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">苹果</div></figure><p>简短的回答是，你不知道。您可以在大多数手机和 PC 上播放“高分辨率”音频文件，只是您可能无法获得完整的体验。如果您设备的音频接口最高频率为 44.1 或 48kHz（这相当普遍并且涵盖了绝大多数在线音乐），那么您将获得这种体验。如果您想以更高的采样率和位深度（即分辨率）欣赏音乐，您需要一个支持它的接口和有线耳机。</p><p>值得指出的是，“无损”和“高分辨率”是相关术语，但不是一回事，并且会因服务而异。 Apple 使用<em>经过</em>压缩的<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apple_Lossless">ALAC 编码</a>，但不会“损失”质量（不同于无处不在的 .aac 或 .mp3 文件格式）。 CD 通常被掌握到至少 16 位/44.1kHz，这是 Apple 用于定义无损的基准。在音频界，普遍的共识是高分辨率是采样率高<em>于</em>44.1kHz 的任何东西。不过，该术语越来越多地用于 96kHz 及以上的频率。</p><p>当然，这不仅仅与 Apple 的新流媒体格式有关。外部 DAC 和音频接口是获得最佳音质和全面提升聆听体验的好方法。特别是如果您想进入更奇特（阅读：昂贵）耳机的世界，因为它们通常甚至需要 DAC 来提供足够干净的信号来驱动它们。对于发烧级耳机，手机或笔记本电脑的内置声音芯片通常无法提供所需的音效。</p><h3>好的，但我不能只使用手机的耳机适配器吗？</h3><p>不，嗯，是的，但见上文。 Lightning 或 USB-C 至 3.5 毫米耳机适配器通常<em>是</em>音频接口，您以 7 美元购买的大多数耳机（或包装盒中免费提供）不支持超过 48kHz / 24 位的高分辨率音频。 Android 稍微复杂一些，因为一些适配器是“被动的”，实际上只是将您连接到手机的内部 DAC，就像老式耳机一样。其他（活跃的）内置 DAC，祝您好运，找出您的特定手机和内置适配器提供的功能。 （提示：将它连接到 PC 上，看看它是否作为音频接口出现。如果出现，您可能会在那里找到一些详细信息）。</p><h2>什么是“DAC”？ </h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-06/0d3d0720-c9e1-11eb-bff3-69fe89e400be" alt="2021 年适用于 Apple Music Lossless 的最佳 DAC。" data-uuid="cc10a2f6-107a-3836-bf33-ce128213418b"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">比利·斯蒂尔 / Engadget</div></figure><p>数模转换器从您的手机或计算机获取数字 (D) 音乐，并将其转换 (C) 为您可以听到的模拟 (A) 声音。所有手机和 PC 都有它们，但由于手机转为 USB-C、Lightning 或蓝牙播放音乐，转换该信号的任务通常外包给您的适配器或无线耳机。</p><p> DAC 可用于手机、笔记本电脑和台式机，但往往比常规的外部音频接口简单得多。一个基本区别是 DAC 通常仅用于收听，而音频接口可能具有用于插入麦克风和乐器的端口（但外部音频接口在技术上也是 DAC）。</p><p> DAC 的好处是它们往往很轻，使它们更适合移动使用，尽管它在 iPhone 上仍然有点棘手，因为您仍然可能需要添加另一个加密狗才能使其与 Lightning 兼容。此外，并非所有 DAC 都支持所有更高的音频分辨率。大多数 DAC 都需要外部电源或板载电池，但有些 DAC 可以使用您插入的任何设备的电源——在这种情况下，预计会影响您的电池寿命。以下是我们针对各种场景的一些选择。</p><h2>最适合寻求简单、实惠选项的 Android 用户：Ugreen USB-C 至 3.5 毫米耳机适配器</h2><p><core-commerce id="886569e1f9a3475faccbe56b4ec3a5e4" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>好的，您期待的是真正的舷外机，我们首先向您展示一个基本的适配器？是的，因为<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDgyV0c1VlRLP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLWlvLTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI3MmE4OWIwYS0wM2Q0LTRkMjctOTdhNi03ZmI4YTg1YjI1NDMifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAcHj8mwWLcaFRqO1pWFQ54fJF7kdWsAm9fcLf7ptNwtb&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB082WG5VTK">这个</a>支持 96kHz 音频（24 位），而且非常简单。只需插入您的 USB-C 设备（或带有……适配器的 USB-A），连接耳机即可。没有按钮，没有控件，没有任何东西可以充电。</p><p>虽然这款加密狗不支持 192kHz，但提高到 96kHz 仍然属于“高分辨率”音频类别，其超低配置和易用性使其成为那些想要音质提升而不需要的人的绝佳选择全口径外部 DAC。</p><p>当然，这款经济实惠的 DAC 最适合带有 USB-C 端口的设备，例如 iPad Pro、MacBook 或大多数 Android 手机。如前所述，您的 Android 可能已经支持高分辨率音频，您只需要一个简单的无源加密狗，但考虑到这款产品的价格和质量，至少您知道您得到了什么，因为音频的具体细节通常很难找到对每部 Android 手机的支持。</p><p>不利的一面是，该适配器对驱动高阻抗耳机的帮助不大，因此不太适合真正需要更多功率来驱动他们最喜欢的耳机的发烧友。我在 Android 手机和 iMac 上都使用过它，效果很好，但在 Apple 电脑上，您需要先进入音频/MIDI 设置，以确保获得最高质量。</p><h2>最适合高端耳机的流线型桌面使用：Apogee Groove </h2><p><core-commerce id="59eee8c768b3497eac9252eb07185774" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> Apogee 装备通常在工作室中找到。 <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAblx_ZTON-Q47x-Aha3xqGii2T-zUpoloIgxMwu5JlWc&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FApogee-GROOVE-Portable-Headphone-Amplifier%2Fdp%2FB00XR5HRBU">Groove</a>将公司数十年的音频经验融入到高度便携的 DAC 中，非常适合那些希望为台式机或笔记本电脑选择轻量级选项的人。我们通过支持 192 kHz（24 位）来提高音质，这将涵盖 Apple 新的无损服务的所有内容。</p><p>将 iPhone 连接到 Groove 稍微复杂一些。它工作得很好，但你需要像<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAZi7j3TMFgAVeyVuZ_x_pj57eHNV_q4VFQaJK8OWf_2K&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FApple-Lightning-USB3-Camera-Adapter%2Fdp%2FB01F7KJDIM">Apple Camera kit</a>这样的东西，因为它需要外部电源。简而言之，它有点“dongly”，但如果你首先想要桌面上的东西，它就可以工作，它可以在 iPhone 上完成双重任务。 Android 支持有点碰运气，但您仍然需要一种在使用时为其供电的方法。</p><p>设置完成后，只需插入耳机即可。 The rubberized base of the Groove stops it from shifting around on your desk, and the large buttons make controlling volume a breeze, with LED feedback to show you volume levels.</p><p> Audio sounds dynamic, with a generous bump in gain over whatever you&#39;re plugging it into likely offers. The frequency response is flat meaning you get out exactly what you put in audio-wise, making this a great choice if the connectivity (and price) matches your specific use case.</p><h2> Best for power and portability: AudioQuest Dragonfly Cobalt </h2><p><core-commerce id="a0720e6179954daba5b49ff2fa0002a9" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> Bar the Ugreen dongle, the <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAeG4UbuZMuN3ygYyPi8C1jZCMruqZNw8YTD7CcL0YKX0&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FAudioQuest-Dragonfly-USB-Headphone-Amplifier%2Fdp%2FB07T3HSD9Z">Dragonfly</a> is easily the smallest, most portable device on this list. And better yet, it almost certainly works with your phone, PC or laptop and won&#39;t require a dedicated power supply (despite the lack of a built-in battery). You&#39;ll still need an adapter for phones (USB-A to Lightning or USB-A to USB-C for Android) but otherwise, it&#39;s plug and play. There&#39;s no volume control, just one 3.5mm headphone jack and a color-changing LED (to tell you what sample rate the track you&#39;re listening to is using).</p><p> At $300, it&#39;s a pricey proposition, but the cable spaghetti of some devices or the sheer heft of others, means the Dragonfly&#39;s small footprint and rugged simplicity make it refreshingly discreet and simple. AudioQuest also offers two cheaper models, <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9BdWRpb1F1ZXN0LURyYWdvbkZseS1CbGFjay1QcmVhbXAtSGVhZHBob25lL2RwL0IwMURQNUpISEk_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8taW8tMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjcyYTg5YjBhLTAzZDQtNGQyNy05N2E2LTdmYjhhODViMjU0MyJ9&amp;signature=AQAAATb1meda6ExmxPGOZBcMTOdJK1eFxlCjgidyPHq6H5bo&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FAudioQuest-DragonFly-Black-Preamp-Headphone%2Fdp%2FB01DP5JHHI">starting at $100</a> that are likely more than good enough for most people.</p><p> Don&#39;t let the Dragonfly&#39;s size and lack of controls fool you, the Cobalt throws out some serious, high quality sound. According to AudioQuest, the maximum resolution has been intentionally limited to 96kHz for the “optimal” experience, and that&#39;s plenty enough to cover what you&#39;ll get from most music services.</p><p> The output from the in-built headphone amp will make your phone&#39;s audio feel positively wimpy by comparison, and the powerful internal sound processing chip delivers crystal clear audio with a wide soundstage across a range of genres and formats.</p><p> One extra trick up the Dragonfly&#39;s sleeve is native support for Master Quality Authenticated (MQA) files. This is the preferred format of Tidal, so if that&#39;s your service of choice, the Dragonfly is ideal.</p><h2> Best for super high resolution: Fiio Q3 </h2><p><core-commerce id="00a4c9369d9d4c6ebd8167904c6f89a1" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> Fiio has been a popular name in the portable DAC scene for a while now, and for good reason. The products deliver solid audio quality, support all manner of resolutions and are compatible with a wide range of devices. The <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9GaWlPLVEzLUFLNDQ2MkRBQy1UZWNobm9sb2d5LU1vYmlsZVBob25lL2RwL0IwOEs4R1hDSko_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8taW8tMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjcyYTg5YjBhLTAzZDQtNGQyNy05N2E2LTdmYjhhODViMjU0MyJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAaovRcXZxP_3kx2spSSN8UF6YMp7OvzdlgV3zOVvNCdJ&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FFiiO-Q3-AK4462DAC-Technology-MobilePhone%2Fdp%2FB08K8GXCJJ">Q3</a> is bigger than the previous options on this list (it&#39;s about 1cm shorter than an iPhone 4), but remains fully portable. There are even some goofy silicone bands so you can strap it to your phone, rather than have a flappy, heavy appendage.</p><p> For users on the go, the Q3&#39;s built-in battery (good for about eight hours) means you won&#39;t need to drain the power on whatever you&#39;re plugging it into. It also means mobile users won&#39;t need a dreaded second cable. Throw in support for <em>three</em> different size headphone jacks (sadly, ¼-inch isn&#39;t one of them) and you have a DAC that will serve you souped-up sounds wherever you are and whatever you&#39;re listening to.</p><p> There isn&#39;t a display, which you might expect for something this size, but there is an LED that changes color when you&#39;re listening to something higher than 48kHz, so you can tell which tracks in your streaming service&#39;s library really are higher-res. The dedicated volume control doubles as a power knob and there&#39;s also a “bass boost” switch just like the good old days. On top of the USB-C input, there&#39;s also the option for analog audio sources via the 3.5mm port.</p><p> Even if you&#39;re not listening to high sample rate music, the Q3 sounds fantastic. The difference in volume, punch and dynamic range that comes through in songs that sounded flat and dense when listening directly through a phone or laptop was remarkable. Throw in support for all the hertz and bit-depths that you&#39;ll likely ever need and what&#39;s not to like? Especially as the Q3 comes in cheaper than some of the less capable options in this guide (the slight extra heft will be a key factor here).</p><h2> Best for high resolution / fans of Tidal: iFi Hip Dac </h2><p><core-commerce id="591b2c3fc9ec41d393d8f2bea9acf2f3" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> If this were a spec race, it&#39;d be a photo finish between Fiio&#39;s Q3 and <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL2Ftem4udG8vM3BEamhzSSIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNzJhODliMGEtMDNkNC00ZDI3LTk3YTYtN2ZiOGE4NWIyNTQzIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAWxZgLNDfZaX_oy-kERbUADHms0MmEphwQ3TVnJMF0AM&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Famzn.to%2F3pDjhsI" class="rapid-with-clickid">iFi&#39;s Hip Dac</a> . Like the Q3, the Hip Dac blows right past support for 192kHz right up to 384kHz. It also offers balanced output via 4.4mm headphones which is rare to find on consumer headphones, but some higher-end cans offer it for those who want to eliminate any potential interference. There&#39;s also an internal battery, bass boost and a very similar form-factor to the Q3.</p><p> For anyone interested in either of these two it might come down to a single feature. Be that the highest sample rate it can support (Q3 wins) or its ability to decode Tidal&#39;s MQA files (in which case, you want the Hip Dac).</p><p> The sound out of this thing takes on the Q3 blow for blow and even the same knurled volume control is here. But let&#39;s be honest, the fact it looks like (and was named after) a hip flask is clearly also a major selling point. Though it&#39;s worth mentioning the Hip Dac takes a female USB cable, supplied in the box. But this does mean you&#39;ll need to use the Camera Kit to get into the iPhone, whereas the Q3 works with one single provided cable.</p><p> Regardless, it&#39;s another robust option that will more than cover most bases for most people. As with the Q3, the internal battery means you won&#39;t need to feed it power while in use (estimated eight hours) and connecting it to your phone or computer is the same; as long as you can pipe a USB cable into it, you&#39;re good to go.</p><h2> Best for desktop warriors: Focusrite Scarlett 2i2 </h2><p><core-commerce id="c30b6ef7e65f49709b361f36bd0d1964" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> Only looking for a desktop DAC? Then a good old fashioned audio interface might be the best choice for you. <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9Gb2N1c3JpdGUtU2NhcmxldHQtQXVkaW8tSW50ZXJmYWNlLVRvb2xzL2RwL0IwN1FSNzNUNjY_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8taW8tMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjcyYTg5YjBhLTAzZDQtNGQyNy05N2E2LTdmYjhhODViMjU0MyJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAcKAc__ifo0JpOUhioAN7N8pPf-tOnA5SqurGvoHkHhV&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FFocusrite-Scarlett-Audio-Interface-Tools%2Fdp%2FB07QR73T66">Focusrite&#39;s Scarlett</a> series has near-legendary status at this point and an eye-wateringly high review ratio on Amazon for a good reason: It does what it does very very well.</p><p> Most current laptops and desktops can probably handle at least 96kHz audio, but with the Scarlett you can be sure you are getting the full 192kHz when available and the dedicated audio processors and headphone amps will do a much better job of it.</p><p> The main benefit here is the general upgrade you will be giving to your PC. Not only will your listening experience be enhanced, but you&#39;ll be able to plug in microphones and instruments if streaming or recording are your thing, all in one device and all for about the same price as some of the more mobile-oriented devices on this list.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/the-best-dac-for-lossless-high-resolution-music-iphone-android-160056147.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/the-best-dac-for-lossless-high-resolution-music-iphone-android-160056147.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 72a89b0a-03d4-4d27-97a6-7fb8a85b2543</guid><dc:creator> James Trew</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher> Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Fri, 26 May 2023 15:00:05 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1685113205</ingested><modified> 2023-05-26T15:00:15+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Audio Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Handheld & Connected Devices]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|James Trew]]></category><media:content height="1333" medium="image" url=